<h1>Green Puffs</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>1/2 cup rolled oats</li>
<li>2 tablespoons flaxseed meal</li>
<li>1 1/2 cups spinach</li>
<li>1 banana</li>
<li>1/2 cup unsweetened applesauce</li>
<li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
<li>1/2 cup raisins</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.</li>
<li>Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.</li>
<li>Place oats in a blender and blend into a fine meal.</li>
<li>Add flaxseed meal to a small bowl and mix with 3 tablespoons water to make a paste. Add more water if needed.</li>
<li>Add flaxseed paste and all remaining ingredients to blender.</li>
<li>Blend until well combined. Consistency should be similar to pancake batter.</li>
<li>Scoop spoonfuls (about 2 tablespoons each) onto parchment-lined baking sheet. You should end up with 16-20 dollops.</li>
<li>Bake for 10 minutes at 375 degrees F, lower heat to 250 degrees F and bake for another 15 minutes.</li>
<li>Puffs will still be a little soft when you take them out, but will firm up a little bit when they cool.</li>
</ol>
